    "plan_content": "The plan is ready for your review. Here's a quick summary:\n\n**8 files modified** across 3 code paths (V0 legacy, V1 GPU, V1 TPU):\n\n1. **`vllm/sampling_params.py`** ŌĆö Add `top_a: float = 0.0` field with docstring, validation (`[0, 1]`), greedy override, and `from_optional()` support\n2. **`vllm/v1/sample/logits_processor.py`** ŌĆö New `TopALogitsProcessor` class (mirrors `MinPLogitsProcessor` exactly), registered as an `argmax_invariant` processor. This is the cleanest approach ŌĆö no changes needed to `gpu_input_batch.py`, V1 `SamplingMetadata`, or V1 `sampler.py`\n3. **`vllm/model_executor/sampling_metadata.py`** ŌĆö Add `top_as` tensor to V0 `SamplingTensors`\n4. **`vllm/model_executor/layers/sampler.py`** ŌĆö Add `_apply_top_a()` function (same formula as `_apply_min_p`), wire into V0 `forward()`\n5. **`vllm/v1/worker/tpu_input_batch.py`** ŌĆö Add top_a tensors/tracking (mirrors `min_p` pattern)\n6. **`vllm/v1/sample/tpu/metadata.py`** ŌĆö Add `top_a` to TPU metadata\n7. **`vllm/v1/sample/tpu/sampler.py`** ŌĆö Add `apply_top_a()` method\n8. **`vllm/v1/spec_decode/utils.py`** ŌĆö Mark `top_a > 0` as spec-decode-unsupported",
